# Requirements First Orchestration

## Lightweight Direct-Do

When requirements are clear, scope is tiny, single-file, no cross-module spread, no trade-offs, no migration/infra risk: handle directly without creating docs.
Typical: copy/comment fixes, single config change, single-file bug fix, clear lint/test fix, simple command execution.
If hidden complexity surfaces or shared files / frozen contracts are touched, escalate to requirement/task orchestration immediately.

## Non-Trivial Work

- Before planning, create or locate a requirement: project-level → `PROJECT_REQUIREMENTS.md`; task-level → `req-*.md`; closed → `archive/`.
- Active index: `REQUIREMENT_CENTER.md` (paired with `TASK_CENTER.md`).
- Requirements must be concise, in Chinese, aligned with user intent. Structure: `用户需求`, `当前进展` (progress/status/blockers/next), `待确认` (None if empty).
- `当前进展` may legitimately say `阻塞项: None` and `下一步: None / 归档 / 等待新需求`; do not invent fake blockers, fake confirmations, or placeholder next steps just to satisfy the template.
- New requirements default to `needs-confirmation`; mark `confirmed` only after explicit user approval. Progress-only updates do not downgrade status.
- Task docs record linked requirement path and inherit confirmed requirement understanding.
- Sync concise progress back to requirement at key milestones, on blockers, or before ending conversation.
- When a workflow has a `docs/workspace/<workflow>/` folder, sync decision-relevant findings (trade-offs, options, human-intervention needs) to workspace; parent orchestrator owns workspace writes.
- Resume truth follows lifecycle first: check `REQUIREMENT_CENTER.md`, `TASK_CENTER.md`, and workspace dashboard/archive placement before treating any root doc as active. Archived docs are provenance, not active handoff.
- When a scope is objectively complete and no real active follow-up remains, archive requirement/task/workspace in the same turn instead of leaving root-level placeholders.
- If requirement is unclear or execution would expand scope, stop and confirm with user first.
